ggs":["mineral"],"flavor":[{"version":"gold","text":"Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composi\u00ad tion appears to be closer to a rock than a plant."},{"version":"silver","text":"It disguises it\u00ad self as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining."},{"version":"crystal","text":"If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it's a SUDOWOODO, not a tree. It hides from the rain."},{"version":"ruby","text":"SUDOWOODO camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because the forelegs remain green throughout the year, the POK\u00e9MON is easily identified as a fake during the winter."},{"version":"sapphire","text":"SUDOWOODO camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because the forelegs remain green throughout the year, the POK\u00e9MON is easily identified as a fake during the winter."},{"version":"emerald","text":"It mimics a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. But since its forelegs remain green throughout the year, it is easily identified as a fake in the winter."},{"version":"firered","text":"It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining."},{"version":"leafgreen","text":"Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears to be closer to a rock than a plant."},{"version":"diamond","text":"Despite appearing to be a tree, its body is closer to rocks and stones. It is very weak to water."},{"version":"pearl","text":"It stands along paths pretending to be a tree. If it starts raining, it seems to disappear."},{"version":"platinum","text":"To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain."},{"version":"heartgold","text":"Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation."},{"version":"soulsilver","text":"It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining."},{"version":"black","text":"To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain."},{"version":"white","text":"To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain."},{"version":"black-2","text":"To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain."},{"version":"white-2","text":"To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain."},{"version":"x","text":"Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation."},{"version":"y","text":"It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining."},{"version":"omega-ruby","text":"Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pok\u00e9mon is easily identified as a fake during the winter."},{"version":"alpha-sapphire","text":"Sudowoodo camouflages itself as a tree to avoid being attacked by enemies. However, because its hands remain green throughout the year, the Pok\u00e9mon is easily identified as a fake during the winter."},{"version":"sun","text":"To avoid attack, it mimics a tree. It will run off if splashed with water, which it hates."},{"version":"moon","text":"Apparently, the larger the green parts of this Pok\u00e9mon, the more collectors value it. It\u2019s a particular favorite among elderly people."},{"version":"ultra-sun","text":"It\u2019s so popular with the elderly that there\u2019s a magazine devoted to this Pok\u00e9mon. Fans obsess over the particular length and angle of its arms."},{"version":"ultra-moon","text":"The result of its holding the same pose all the time is arms that have become supple yet strong."},{"version":"sword","text":"If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it\u2019s a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain."},{"version":"shield","text":"It disguises itself as a tree to avoid attack. It hates water, so it will disappear if it starts raining."},{"version":"legends-arceus","text":"Though it pretends to be a tree, it fails to fool even children. To the touch, its body feels more like rock than tree bark. Sudowoodo's extreme aversion to water merits special note."}],"evo":{"name":"bonsly","level":0,"min_level":null,"trigger":null,"item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":null,"known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":null,"turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[{"name":"sudowoodo","level":1,"min_level":null,"trigger":"level-up","item":null,"held_item":null,"known_move":"mimic","known_move_type":null,"location":null,"min_affection":null,"min_beauty":null,"min_happiness":null,"needs_overworld_rain":false,"time_of_day":"","turn_upside_down":false,"evolves_to":[]}]},"sprite":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/185.png","shiny":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PokeAPI/sprites/master/sprites/pokemon/shiny/185.png","capture":65,"happiness":70,"growth":"medium","gender":4,"hatch":20,"ev":{"defense":2},"forms":[]}